M.definition: A person who belongs to the sex that normally produces sperm.

F.definition: A person who belongs to the sex that normally produces ova.

U.definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused.

UNDIFFERENTIATED.definition: Sex could not be determined; not clearly one or the other.

AMERICAN INDIAN OR ALASKA NATIVE.definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of North and South America (including Central America), and who maintains tribal affiliation or community attachment.

ASIAN.definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of the Far East, Southeast Asia, or the Indian subcontinent.

BLACK OR AFRICAN AMERICAN.definition: A person having origins in any of the Black racial groups of Africa.

NATIVE HAWAIIAN OR OTHER PACIFIC ISLANDE.submission_value: NATIVE HAWAIIAN OR OTHER PACIFIC ISLANDER
NATIVE HAWAIIAN OR OTHER PACIFIC ISLANDE.definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of Hawaii, Guam, Samoa, or other Pacific Islands.
NATIVE HAWAIIAN OR OTHER PACIFIC ISLANDE.nci_preferred_term: Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander

WHITE.definition: A person having origins in any of the original peoples of Europe, the Middle East, or North Africa.

OTHER.definition: A race category not captured by the other specific race categories.

MULTIPLE.definition: A person who identifies with two or more races.

UNKNOWN.definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused.

HISPANIC OR LATINO.definition: A person of Cuban, Mexican, Puerto Rican, South or Central American, or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race.

NOT HISPANIC OR LATINO.definition: A person not of Cuban, Mexican, Puerto Rican, South or Central American, or other Spanish culture or origin, regardless of race.

UNKNOWN.definition: Not known, not observed, not recorded, or refused.

N.definition: The non-affirmative response to a question.

Y.definition: The affirmative response to a question.

GBR.definition: United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland

YEARS.definition: A period of time equal to 365.25 days.

MONTHS.definition: A period of time approximately equal to 30.44 days.

WEEKS.definition: A period of time equal to 7 days.

DAYS.definition: A period of time equal to 24 hours.

HOURS.definition: A period of time equal to 60 minutes.

ORAL.definition: Administration to or by way of the mouth.

INTRAVENOUS.definition: Administration within or into a vein or veins.

TOPICAL.definition: Administration to a particular spot on the outer surface of the body.

TRANSDERMAL.definition: Administration through the dermal layer of the skin.

NASAL.definition: Administration to or by way of the nose.

MILD.definition: An adverse event that is easily tolerated by the subject, causing minimal discomfort and not interfering with everyday activities.

MODERATE.definition: An adverse event that is sufficiently discomforting to interfere with normal everyday activities.

SEVERE.definition: An adverse event that prevents normal everyday activities.

RECOVERED/RESOLVED.definition: The event has resolved or the subject has recovered.

RECOVERING/RESOLVING.definition: The event is resolving or the subject is recovering.

NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED.definition: The event has not resolved and the subject has not recovered.

RECOVERED/RESOLVED WITH SEQUELAE.definition: The event resolved with clinically significant residual effects.

UNKNOWN.definition: The outcome of the event is not known.

kg.definition: A basic unit of mass in the International System of Units equal to 1000 grams.

g.definition: A metric unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a kilogram.

mg.definition: A metric unit of mass equal to one thousandth of a gram.

cm.definition: A metric unit of length equal to one hundredth of a meter.

in.definition: A traditional unit of length equal to 2.54 centimeters.

beats/min.definition: Heart rate measured in beats per minute.

breaths/min.definition: Respiratory rate measured in breaths per minute.

10^9/L.definition: 10 to the ninth power per liter.

10^12/L.definition: 10 to the twelfth power per liter.

%.definition: A fraction or ratio expressed as part of 100.

mL.definition: A metric unit of volume equal to one thousandth of a liter.

sec.definition: A unit of time equal to one sixtieth of a minute.

DOSE NOT CHANGED.definition: The dose of study treatment was not changed.

DOSE REDUCED.definition: The dose of study treatment was reduced.

DOSE INCREASED.definition: The dose of study treatment was increased.

NOT APPLICABLE.definition: Determination of action taken is not relevant.

UNKNOWN.definition: The action taken is not known.

HIGH.definition: Above the upper limit of normal.

LOW.definition: Below the lower limit of normal.

HIGH HIGH.definition: Above the upper limit of the clinically significant range.

LOW LOW.definition: Below the lower limit of the clinically significant range.

SITTING.definition: A body position where the subject is seated.

STANDING.definition: A body position where the subject is upright on their feet.

SUPINE.definition: A body position where the subject is lying face up.

DURING/AFTER.definition: Starting during and continuing after the reference period.

ONGOING.definition: Continuing at the time of the report.

COMPLETED.definition: The subject completed the study as planned.

SCREEN FAILURE.definition: The subject did not meet study entry criteria.

ADVERSE EVENT.definition: The subject discontinued due to an adverse event.

DEATH.definition: The subject died during the study.

LACK OF EFFICACY.definition: The subject discontinued due to lack of therapeutic effect.

LOST TO FOLLOW-UP.definition: The subject could not be contacted for follow-up.

PHYSICIAN DECISION.definition: The investigator decided to discontinue the subject.

PROTOCOL VIOLATION.definition: The subject violated the study protocol.

WITHDRAWAL BY SUBJECT.definition: The subject chose to withdraw from the study.

OTHER.definition: Other reason for disposition not specified.

CAPSULE.definition: A solid dosage form consisting of a shell and a filling.

CREAM.definition: A semisolid emulsion for external application.

GEL.definition: A semisolid system in which a liquid is contained in a matrix.

INJECTION.definition: A sterile preparation intended for parenteral use.

LOTION.definition: A liquid preparation for external application.

OINTMENT.definition: A semisolid preparation for external application.

PATCH.definition: A drug delivery system applied to the skin.

POWDER.definition: A solid consisting of finely divided particles.

SOLUTION.definition: A liquid preparation containing one or more dissolved substances.

SPRAY.definition: A liquid minutely divided as by a jet of air or steam.

SUPPOSITORY.definition: A solid body for insertion into a body cavity.

SUSPENSION.definition: A liquid preparation of particles dispersed in a vehicle.

SYRUP.definition: A concentrated aqueous preparation of a sugar.

TABLET.definition: A solid dosage form containing medicinal substances.

BLOOD.definition: A fluid that circulates through the body.

PLASMA.definition: The fluid portion of blood after cells are removed.

SERUM.definition: The fluid portion of blood after coagulation.

URINE.definition: The fluid excreted by the kidneys.

WHOLE BLOOD.definition: Blood that has not been separated into components.

CEREBROSPINAL FLUID.definition: The fluid surrounding the brain and spinal cord.

SCREENING.definition: The period during which subjects are evaluated for eligibility.

RUN-IN.definition: A period before randomization for baseline stabilization.

TREATMENT.definition: The period during which treatment is administered.

FOLLOW-UP.definition: The period after treatment for monitoring.

HEAD.definition: The upper part of the body.

NECK.definition: The part of the body between the head and trunk.

CHEST.definition: The area between the neck and abdomen.

ABDOMEN.definition: The part of the body between the chest and pelvis.

BACK.definition: The posterior surface of the trunk.

HAND.definition: The terminal part of the upper limb.

FOOT.definition: The terminal part of the lower limb.
